txt.en: 'There they are!'
'You'll not be getting away from us this time, Mr. Baggins!'
'Brigands! Help!'
'Keep away, you brutes!'
'Got you at last! You've got nowhere to run.'
'You'll be coming to Archet with us, all of you. The Rider will decide your fate there!'
'Oh!'
'Ouch!'
'Who goes there?'
'Who are you, and what do you want?'
'You startled me, that's all.'
'There's an odd chill in the air tonight -- very strange. Do you feel it?'
'We'll both feel safer if you come along with me. Do you know how to fight, [placeholder]?'
'Eek! Spiders!'
'Try coming at me, [placeholder]!'
'How I detest spiders!'
'Well done! You ought to consider being a Bounder yourself someday!'
'Phew... no more spiders. Let's press on!'
'I hate spiders....'
'I don't see any more spiders! Hooray!'
'You just need a weapon of some sort.'
'This is the last door until we get to the road!'
'Mundo Sackville-Baggins! Celandine Brandybuck! What are you doing here?'
'What does it look like, you ninny? We are being chased!'
'What does it look like, you ninny?'
'We are being chased by brigands! Do something about it!'
'Come, let's cut through the farm! We can lock them out!'
'Back, wraith! Begone!'
'No!'
'Hsss, enough!'
'Enough!'
'This is not the end, DÃºnadan.'
'Come, hobbits. It is safe now.'
'Poor Amdir!'
'Hobbits seem to turn up in the most unlikely places, Bounder Boffin!'
Brigand Leader
'You villains! What do you want with Mundo?'
'Your Mr. Baggins is wanted by someone who is lending us great aid in exchange for finding him.'
'But-but there are spiders behind that door, and a terrible horseman on the road! We only just escaped!'
'Are there any other hobbits waiting for rescue in this perilous place, Mr. Boffin?'
'No indeed, Mr. Ranger! Just me, [placeholder], Celandine, and Mundo!'
'That is a relief! Now come with me, both of you.'
'Amdir!'
'Strider! I cannot hold him back, my friend!'
'The door is locked! Hold fast, Amdir!'
'O help us!'
'Strange? But it is a lovely night for a stroll!'
'Hush, Pippin.... What do you mean, strange? Have you seen anything odd along the road?'
'Mercy!'
'Mercy, what is that?'
'You don't need to tell me that twice!'
'Th-there aren't no B-bagginses in these parts, sir!'
'Gracious me! Did you see that, [placeholder]?'
'L-let's get out of here!'
'Odo's farm! I'll get this door open, and we can cut through....'
'Got it!'
'Here is the satchel I dropped when you startled me.'
'Inside is a spare weapon. You should loot it for yourself, and then equip it to use it.'
'Oh my! Did you hear something?'
'There, down the road! Who could that be?'
'More travellers at night! And who might you be?'
'More travellers at night! And who might you be?'
'Well met, my good bounder! My name is... Underhill.'
'Ah! At last.'
'And here are my fellow travellers, Samwise Gamgee and Peregrin Took.'
'I've never seen so many hobbits out of bed! And on such a strange night, too....'
'Why, I've never seen so many hobbits out of bed! And on such a strange night, too.'
'But-but there are spiders behind that door, and a terrible horseman on the road! We only just escaped!'
'Get them!'
